parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause loud noises, decreased engine performance, and potentially lead to carbon monoxide poisoning if the exhaust system leaks into the passenger compartment.
symptoms: Exhaust tail pipe failure
engine backfires on deceleration
engine knocks under moderate acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A valve sticking open can cause engine performance issues, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage if not addressed.
symptoms: Valve sticking open on rear cylinder
engine knocking or tapping sounds
decreased engine performance
decreased fuel efficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the wheel rim can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. Additionally, the rim's failure to hit the brake caliper can cause further damage to the braking system, compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: The wheel rim splits or cracks
often without warning
while traveling at moderate to high speeds (50-60 mph)
particularly when exiting the interstate. There may be no visible signs of tire damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Damage to the brake caliper can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake caliper is hit by the failed wheel rim
potentially causing damage to the braking system. This may result in reduced braking performance
unusual noises
or vibrations when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the horn can lead to reduced safety on the road, as the driver may not be able to alert other drivers or pedestrians in emergency situations.
symptoms: The horn does not work occasionally
the horn works intermittently
the horn produces a weak or faint sound
the horn does not respond to button press.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent stalling can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies suddenly
the engine shuts off without warning
the vehicle hesitates or stumbles before stalling
the vehicle stalls frequently
especially when idling or driving at low speeds.

the vehicle stalls frequently
especially when idling or driving at low speeds

the vehicle stalls frequently

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Side Stand (Kickstand) Failure Due to Vibration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side stand (kickstand) can cause the motorcycle to fall over, potentially resulting in damage to the vehicle, injury to the rider, or even accidents.
symptoms: The motorcycle falls over while on its side stand
the side stand collapses due to vibration
the motorcycle is unstable while on its side stand
the vibration from the engine causes the side stand to fail.
